# Error Handling

## Taxonomy
- Distinguish **expected business errors** (validation, not-found...) from **system errors** (bugs, downstream failures).
- User-facing vs internal errors: different messages; never leak internal detail outward.

## Verifiable rules
- **No silent catch.** A caught error must be logged (with the correlation ID) or re-thrown with context.
- Wrap errors with context when crossing a boundary; don't swallow the original stack trace.
- Retry only transient errors (network/timeout) with backoff; never retry business errors.

